========================================================================
                                 PROMPT:
========================================================================                                    
The Magic 8-Ball is a super popular toy used for fortune-telling or seeking advice, developed in the 1950s!

Write a C++ program that will output a random fortune each time it executes.

Magic 8-Ball, should I do this project?

The answers inside a standard Magic 8-Ball are:

    It is certain.
    It is decidedly so.
    Without a doubt.
    Yes - definitely.
    You may rely on it.
    As I see it, yes.
    Most likely.
    Outlook good.
    Yes.
    Signs point to yes.
    Reply hazy, try again.
    Ask again later.
    Better not tell you now.
    Cannot predict now.
    Concentrate and ask again.
    Don't count on it.
    My reply is no.
    My sources say no.
    Outlook not so good.
    Very doubtful.
========================================================================
                            LEARNING OUTCOMES:
========================================================================
1. Introduction to functions in std::cstdlib specifically srand() and rand()
2. Conditionals (if/else if/else)
3. Throwing exceptions using std::stdexcept
